            <head>Rosine Taneberger</head>
            <div type="page" n="1">
               <head>Page 1 <seg ana="MemBeth_0140-01" />
               </head>
               <p> 
                  II. The married Sist. Rosine Taneberger. 
                  She was Ao 1708 born at Mammendorf in Moravia.
                  Her Vaters name was Geo. Weber. The holy
                  ghost had from her tender youth his work in
                  heart &amp; she spent her time continually  
                  without Rest in her soul. In her 25th. year
                  of Age she married Michel Taneberger. she
                  [has] 2 Boys with him but they died very young. She 
                  very often pineth to hear the Gospel of Jesus
                  Sufferings of Death, therefore she very begged dear
                  God to still her Desire &amp; help her to a Place where
                  she could find rest for her poor soul,then she could
                  not find that in her Mother Country. Ao 1753. the 13th October
                  She got a feeling in her heart to move to Gnaden-
                  frey, they hastened as much as possible &amp; escaped
                  hardly from their pursuers. The 31 of Dec.
                  she arrived here very much rejoiced. Soon after
                  a critical occasion pretty nearly persuadeth
                  her husbands to remove from here to his son.
                  She therefore was so embarrassed &amp; intreated our 
                  Serviour in her Perplexity saying: feared my heart catched a spark 
                  of grace, &amp; instead to become a fire he will be quenched!                  
               </p>
